						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall, central shrine, Vaikuṇṭhavāsa-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 16: 987 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged. It seems to record a sale of some land irrigated by the tank, by the <hi rend="italic">mahāsabhā</hi> of Kiḷinallūr in Oymā-nāḍu to Sāttaṉ Kallaḍigal of Puḍaippākkam in Vēśālippāḍi with the condition that he would arrange to contribute a <hi rend="italic">tūṇi</hi> of paddy from each crop from <hi rend="italic">cheṟu</hi> towards the maintenance of the tank. It is also stated that if there was any default he had to pay a fine to the reigning local lord <hi rend="italic">(kō).</hi></p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 398.</p>						

						</summary>
